\begin_layout Section
Conclusions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The spiral model we have presented is well-known in music theory and experimenta
l psychology 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Shepard1964, Risset1969, Deutsch2008"

\end_inset

.
 However, existing methods in audio signal processing do not fully take
 advantage from its richness, because they either picture pitch on a line
 (e.g.
 MFCC) or on a circle (e.g.
 chroma features).
 In this article, we have shown how spiral scattering can represent the
 transientness of harmonic sounds.
